comments: Caruso (CHI) moves forward slightly prior to marginal body contact occurring with Brunson (NYK) as they approach the pick.
Randle (NYK) establishes himself in Caruso's (CHI) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Randle (NYK) and Caruso (CHI) engage and disengage with one another off-ball.
Randle (NYK) goes to, not through, Caruso (CHI) and marginal contact occurs with Caruso's front prior to Randle stepping back toward the free throw line.
Williams' (CHI) right leg is slightly extended forward when marginal contact occurs with Brunson's (NYK) left leg/foot as Brunson starts his dribble.

Vucevic (CHI) engages and disengages with Robinson (NYK) as Robinson establishes rebounding position in the lane. DeRozan (CHI) brings his hands forward and marginal contact occurs with Robinson's left side after he retrieves the ball.
DeRozan (CHI) raises his right hand and marginal contact occurs with Robinson's (NYK) right forearm as Robinson makes the pass.
Randle (NYK) and Caruso (CHI) engage and disengage with one another off-ball.

Replay review of the foul called on Williams (CHI) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed successful. Williams contests the jump shot attempt and incidental "high-five" contact occurs with Randle (NYK) after the release. Williams would avoid contact with Randle's body if Randle did not extend his left leg forward to initiate the marginal contact. There was not imminent possession and a jump ball at the center circle was assessed.
Brunson (NYK) and DeRozan (CHI) engage and disengage with one another as they approach the screen.
Vucevic (CHI) slightly extends to the side before absorbing the contact that occurs with Brunson (NYK) as the screen is set.
Barrett (NYK) initiates contact with DeRozan's (CHI) right arm during the driving shot attempt.
Williams (CHI) and Randle (NYK) engage and disengage with one another off-ball.
Randle (NYK) establishes himself in Caruso's (CHI) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Randle (NYK) grasps and then quickly releases Caruso's (CHI) left arm following the expiration of the pick.

Caruso (CHI) makes contact with the ball as simultaneous marginal contact occurs with Randle's (NYK) right arm at the end of the drive. Williams (CHI) also makes clean contact with the ball at the end of Randle's drive.
Barrett (NYK) initiates contact across DeRozan's (CHI) right arm after his gather.
Williams (CHI) moves forward slightly prior to marginal body contact occurring with Randle (NYK) off-ball.
Randle (NYK) and Caruso (CHI) engage and disengage with one another off-ball.
Vucevic (CHI) turns his body and initiates contact with Randle (NYK) that affects his shot attempt near the rim.

Randle (NYK) jumps toward the basket with his arms brought forward slightly and marginal contact occurs with Vucevic's (CHI) head as the two come together. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Brunson (NYK) is retreating toward the baseline when marginal body contact occurs with DeRozan (CHI) during the driving shot attempt.
Williams (CHI) is moving alongside Randle's (NYK) path and marginal body contact occurs as Randle drives inside the perimeter.
Williams (CHI) legally contests Randle's (NYK) jump shot attempt.
Williams (CHI) mishandles the inbound pass prior to incidental arm/body contact being made by Randle (NYK) as they come together near the rim.

After communicating with the Replay Center, it was determined Randle's (NYK) shot attempt did not make contact with the rim. A 24 second violation is called on New York and Chicago receives possession with 0.7 seconds remaining.
Randle (NYK) establishes himself in Caruso's (CHI) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Randle (NYK) and Caruso (CHI) engage and disengage with one another in the post.
Caruso (CHI) initiates contact across Randle's (NYK) arms during his upward shooting motion.
Grimes (NYK) brings his left arm outward and marginal contact occurs with DeRozan's (CHI) front as DeRozan moves up the lane line.
Brunson (NYK) extends his leg out and intentionally kicks the ball.

Robinson (NYK) uses a legal bent hand and forearm as he defends Vucevic (CHI) in the post. Robinson then establishes verticality and absorbs the marginal contact that occurs as Vucevic dribbles into the lane thereafter.
Robinson (NYK) maintains verticality and absorbs the contact made with Vucevic (CHI) before cleanly blocking his shot attempt near the rim.

Caruso (CHI) is moving alongside Brunson's (NYK) path and legally contests the driving shot attempt. Vucevic's (CHI) left arm comes outward after the release and marginal contact occurs with Brunson's front as Brunson returns to the floor.
Vucevic (CHI) rests his hand on Robinson's (NYK) left shoulder and quickly releases as they each pursue the rebound.
Williams (CHI) cleanly back-taps the rebound prior to incidental arm contact occurring with Robinson (NYK) or Randle (NYK).

Caruso (CHI) maintains verticality and absorbs the body contact made with Randle (NYK) in the post. DeRozan (CHI) moves forward slightly prior to marginal body contact occurring with Randle simultaneously.

Grimes (NYK) moves alongside DeRozan's (CHI) path and absorbs the marginal body contact that occurs during the drive. Randle (NYK) then comes to double team DeRozan and cleanly dislodges him of the ball before incidental contact occurs.
Grimes' (NYK) left thigh touches the ball last before it goes out of bounds.
Vucevic (CHI) establishes himself in Quickley's (NYK) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Caruso (CHI) turns slightly prior to marginal body contact occurring with Brunson (NYK) as Brunson dribbles along the sideline.
Brunson (NYK) slows his momentum in the corner and avoids making contact with Caruso (CHI).
Quickley (NYK) wraps LaVine's (CHI) upper half during the inbound.
Grimes (NYK) legally contests DeRozan's (CHI) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Correctly called 24 second violation on NYK.
